# Grade 10 Accounting Concepts UI & Backend Expansion

This plan addresses the new feedback in `Validation logs.md` concerning missing question variations (forms of ownership, broad asset/liability examples, journals) and missing interactive formats (Drag & Drop Matching and Word Bank).

## Goal Description
Expand the backend generator to include missing curriculum items (Activity 1 & 3, forms of ownership, comprehensive assets/liabilities, subsidiary journals, mark-up calculations) and introduce three highly engaging, interactive frontend question formats:
1. **Matching** (side-side columns that users can "float/match")
2. **Word Bank** ("pick and place" fill in the blanks)
3. **Calculations** (Cost of sales, Selling Price, Mark-up formulas)

## Proposed Changes

### caps-ai-backend 
#### [MODIFY] [sole_trader_generator.py](file:///C:/Users/princ/fundile-tlassistant-vite/caps-ai-backend/app/utils/grade10_accounting/sole_trader_generator.py)
- **Content Expansion**: Inject new dictionary pools for:
    - Forms of ownership, types of businesses (retail vs service).
    - Source document to Journal mapping (e.g., duplicate invoice -> Debtors Journal).
    - Activity 1 & 3 items (comprehensive breakdown of elements like Packing Material, Favourable Bank Balance, etc.).
- **New Question Type: `match`**
    - Will generate side-by-side matching sets (4-5 pairs).
    - Data structure: `left_items: [{id, text}]`, `right_items: [{id, text}]` (shuffled), `matches: {leftId: rightId}`.
- **New Question Type: `word_bank`**
    - Will provide a block of text with missing keywords, and a "bank" of pills.
    - Data structure: `text_parts: [...]`, `blanks: [{id}]`, `word_bank: [words]`, `answers: {blankId: word}`.
- **New Question Type: `calc`**
    - Dynamically generated mathematical scenarios for Profit Margin, Selling Price, and Cost of Sales.
    - E.g. "If cost price is R20,000 and profit margin is 50%, calculate the Selling Price."

### src/components/workspace/grade10/accounting/sole-trader 
#### [MODIFY] [Grade10AccountingSoleTraderPractice.jsx](file:///C:/Users/princ/fundile-tlassistant-vite/src/components/workspace/grade10/accounting/sole-trader/Grade10AccountingSoleTraderPractice.jsx)
- **Implement Matching UI** 
    - Build a responsive two-column grid.
    - Instead of problematic HTML5 Drag and Drop which routinely fails on mobile and touchscreens, implement a "Select & Snap" mechanism heavily used in modern education apps: user clicks a right-side item, then clicks an empty slot next to a left-side item to snap it in place. (Though if strict drag-and-drop is preferred, we can use native HTML5 drag events).
- **Implement Word Bank UI**
    - Render a bank of words as "pills". User selects a pill and selects a blank line to fill it.
- **Implement Calculation UI**
    - Add rendering support to capture step-by-step calculations and link to the existing `EnhancedMathKeypad`.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Drag and Drop (DnD) APIs via native HTML5 have historically poor support on mobile devices. I propose building the "Matching" and "Word Bank" interactions as **"Click to Select, Click to Place"** (often referred to as tap-to-move). It feels incredibly fast, snappy, and works beautifully across desktop and mobile without adding external drag-and-drop libraries (like `dnd-kit`). 
> Are you comfortable substituting "Drag to Drop" with "Tap to Snap/Place"?

